 of art in the modern age. It is to the historical and conceptual significance of this "off" that this book is dedicated. By focusing on what is outside the frame of a work of art, it offers a comprehensive theory of film, a concise history of American cinema from D.W. Griffith to Quentin Tarantino, and a reflection on the place and significance of film within the arts of modernity in general.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 15. Sep 2020) 0aFraming (Cinematography). 0aMotion picturesxHistoryxUnited StatesxUnited States. 0aMotion picturesxPhilosophy. 0aMotion pictureszUnited StatesxHistory. 4aBruegel. 4aChaplin. 4aGriffith. 4aHawks. 4aShakespeare. 4aTarantino. 4aTarkovsky. 4aframe. 4amodernity. 4aoff-screen. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Film & Video / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUP Complete eBook-Package 2017z978311070369640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781503601611zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781503601611423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781503601611.jpg  a978-3-11-070369-6  SUP Complete eBook-Package 2017b2017  aGBV-deGruyter-alles